{"id":703468126,"lang":"swift","time":"1 month, 2 weeks","timestamp":1653056964,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"136 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/703468126/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"15.9 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * public class TreeNode {\n *     public var val: Int\n *     public var left: TreeNode?\n *     public var right: TreeNode?\n *     public init() { self.val = 0; self.left = nil; self.right = nil; }\n *     public init(_ val: Int) { self.val = val; self.left = nil; self.right = nil; }\n *     public init(_ val: Int, _ left: TreeNode?, _ right: TreeNode?) {\n *         self.val = val\n *         self.left = left\n *         self.right = right\n *     }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    var treeNodeValuesMap: [Int : Bool] = [:]\n    \n    func findTarget(_ root: TreeNode?, _ k: Int) -> Bool {\n        guard let root = root else { return false }\n        \n        let currentNodeValue = root.val\n        let remainingTarget = k - currentNodeValue\n        \n        if treeNodeValuesMap[remainingTarget] != nil { return true }\n        \n        treeNodeValuesMap[currentNodeValue] = true\n        \n        let findTargetInLeft = findTarget(root.left, k)\n        let findTargetInRight = findTarget(root.right, k)\n        \n        return findTargetInLeft || findTargetInRight\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst"}
